<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-08T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1560: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-08T15:00:00-05:00">April 8, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>40. The following telegram has just been received from Geneva:</p>
                        <p>[Here follows text of telegram No. 167, April 7, 9 p.m., from the
                            Minister in Switzerland, printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                        <pb facs="0604" n="516" xml:id="pg_516"/>
                        <p>As this appears to offer a reasonable solution of the difficulty, you are
                            authorized to discuss it with President Olaya and to say that the
                            Department very much hopes that he will find it possible to accept.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>